cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for pose estimation on laboratory animals. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new sim2real domain transfer method, which involves training a pose estimator on the target domain by transferring readily available body keypoint locations from the source domain to generated target images. This involves techniques from machine learning and artificial intelligence, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also deals with neuroscience and the study of neural circuits, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves robotics and the use of simulated models, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics).
